  "What is the most fundamental structural difference between prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells?": "蛋白质细胞和食道细胞之间最根本的结构性区别是什么?",
  "Prokaryotic vs. eukaryotic: the most fundamental division in cellular life. Prokaryotes (Greek: pro = before, karyon = kernel/nucleus): no membrane-bound nucleus — DNA in nucleoid region; no membrane-bound organelles; typically 0.1-10 μm. Eukaryotes (eu = true): membrane-bound nucleus; compartmentalized organelles; typically 10-100 μm. Historical context: Édouard Chatton (1925) first proposed the prokaryote/eukaryote distinction. Carl Woese and George Fox (1977) used 16S/18S rRNA sequences to classify all life into three domains: Bacteria (prokaryotic), Archaea (prokaryotic), Eukarya (eukaryotic). Both cell types share: DNA as genetic material, ribosomes (different sizes), plasma membrane, cytoplasm. The distinction matters because: compartmentalization allows eukaryotes to be larger and more complex (organelles create specialized chemical environments).": "Prokaryotes (Greek: pro = before, karyon = kelmle/nucleus):没有膜内核——核核区域中的DNA;没有膜内核;一般情况下没有膜内核;典型的0.1-10微米。Eukaryotes(e = true):膜内核;分层有机体;典型的10-100微米。历史背景:Edouard Chatton(1925年)首先提议对prokaryote/eukaryote加以区分。Carl Woese和George Fox(1977年)使用16S/18S rNA序列将所有生命分为三个领域:细菌(Prokaytography)、Artaia(Progaryatophy)、Eukarya(etoritology) (e ekuarya(e) (ekugararyaty) 。两种细胞共有:DNA作为遗传材料、ribonome(不同尺寸)、血浆、血质膜、细胞上色质、细胞上的分层。由于:分层可以使eukaryototos成为较大型和较复杂的化学环境,因此)。",
  "What is Gram staining, and why is it one of the most important procedures in clinical microbiology?": "什么是格拉姆染色,为什么这是临床微生物学中最重要的程序之一?",
  "Gram staining — cornerstone of clinical microbiology: (1) Procedure (Hans Christian Gram, 1884): apply crystal violet (primary stain) → iodine mordant (forms CV-I complex) → alcohol decolorization (critical step) → safranin counterstain. (2) Results: Gram-positive: thick peptidoglycan traps CV-I complex → alcohol cannot wash it out → purple. Examples: Staphylococcus, Streptococcus, Bacillus, Clostridium. Gram-negative: thin peptidoglycan + outer membrane dissolved by alcohol → CV-I washed out → safranin counterstain → pink/red. Examples: E. coli, Salmonella, Neisseria, Pseudomonas. (3) Clinical significance: guides empiric antibiotic therapy before culture results return (takes 48-72 hrs). Gram-positive infections: penicillins, cephalosporins, vancomycin. Gram-negative infections: aminoglycosides, fluoroquinolones, carbapenems. (4) Predicts pathogenic mechanisms: Gram-negative outer membrane contains LPS (endotoxin) → triggers severe inflammatory response (septic shock). Gram-positive: exotoxins (many), biofilm formation. (5) Limitations: Mycobacteria are acid-fast (waxy mycolic acid wall — need Ziehl-Neelsen stain). Mycoplasma: no cell wall → cannot be Gram-stained. Still, >130 years later, Gram staining remains the first diagnostic test performed on most clinical bacterial specimens.": "临床微生物学的基石: (1) 程序 (Hans Christian Gram, 1884年): 应用晶体紫(初级污点) 碘固醇(CV-I综合体) 酒精脱色(关键步骤) 沙弗兰尼反盐碱。 (2) 结果: 血压阳性: 厚的peptidologic 陷阱 CV-I综合体 酒精不能冲掉它 紫色。 例如: Stophillococus, Streptococcus, Bacillus, clostridirididium. gramne-nene: 稀薄的peptidocolin 和酒精溶液氨溶液溶液- CVIVI 溶解除色。 例如: E. coli、Salmonella、 Nesisseriyariri、Pseudomononas. (3) 临床影响: 肺炎抗药理学治疗(早于48-72小时) 。 腺阳性感染: 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压-血压- 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压- 血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-血压-性-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血表-性-血表-性-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-性-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血-血",
  "What is the endosymbiotic theory, and how does it explain the evolutionary relationship between prokaryotic and eukaryotic cells?": "内共生理论是什么? 它如何解释 蛋白质细胞和蛋白质细胞之间的进化关系?",
  "Endosymbiotic theory — bridging prokaryotes and eukaryotes: (1) Proposed by Lynn Margulis (1967, initially rejected by 15 journals). Core idea: eukaryotic organelles arose from endosymbiosis (one cell living inside another). (2) Sequence: ancestral eukaryote (large anaerobic archaeon?) engulfed aerobic α-proteobacterium (~2 BYA) → not digested → mutualistic relationship → aerobe provided ATP from O₂ → host provided nutrients and protection → aerobe became mitochondrion. Later, some mitochondria-containing cells engulfed cyanobacteria → cyanobacterium became chloroplast (~1.5 BYA) → gave rise to plant/algae lineages. (3) Evidence: see L7.5 Q27 for comprehensive list (double membranes, circular DNA, 70S ribosomes, binary fission, phylogenetics, gene transfer to nucleus). (4) Ongoing evolution: most original endosymbiont genes transferred to host nucleus over billions of years (endosymbiotic gene transfer). Mitochondria retain only ~37 genes (humans). Chloroplasts retain ~120 genes. Must import ~1,000-1,500 nuclear-encoded proteins through TOM/TIM (mitochondria) or TOC/TIC (chloroplasts) complexes. (5) Present-day examples: Paulinella chromatophora (photosynthetic amoeba with 'chromatophore' acquired from cyanobacteria ~60 MYA — endosymbiosis in progress). (6) Significance: endosymbiosis was the key step that allowed eukaryotic cellular complexity — mitochondrial ATP production provided the energy budget for larger genomes and greater cellular complexity.": "直系生物理论——连接直肠杆菌和eukaryotes:(1) Lynn Margulis 提议(1967年,最初被15个期刊拒绝),核心思想:eukaryyorganielles来自内脏生物(一个细胞生活在另一个细胞中)。 (2) 序列:祖传的eukaryote(大厌氧考古?) 吞没有氧的α蛋白菌(~2 BYA) 120 尚未消化 — — 相互基因关系 obe 提供来自 O2 (主机) 的ATPTP 提供营养和保护 — aerobe 成为 mitochdrion。后来,一些含有mitocondrialy细胞的choomacteria (~1.5 BYAA) 导致植物/藻类血清内脏的内脏。 (3) 证据:更深的立位列表见L simi Q27 (双膜、循环DNA、70Sritooms、二子质裂变、血质变基因转移到核心 。 (4) 最前的进化的进化:正进化的DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA DNA 转基因",
  "A patient develops a persistent catheter-associated urinary tract infection that resists multiple rounds of antibiotic treatment. Microscopy reveals bacteria embedded in a dense matrix of polysaccharides, proteins, and DNA on the catheter surface. What is this structure, and why does it make infections so difficult to treat?": "病人发展了一种耐多轮抗生素治疗的持久性导管相关尿道感染。 微生物揭示了嵌入导管表面的聚沙酸、蛋白质和DNA密集矩阵中的细菌。 这种结构是什么,为什么它使感染如此难以治疗?",
  "Biofilms — prokaryotic community living: (1) Structure: bacteria attach to surface → produce EPS (extracellular polymeric substance) matrix → form 3D architecture with water channels (nutrient delivery) → mature biofilm with microcolonies. EPS composition: polysaccharides, proteins, extracellular DNA (eDNA — structural scaffold). (2) Resistance mechanisms: physical barrier (EPS prevents antibiotic penetration — slow diffusion, adsorption, enzymatic degradation within matrix), metabolic heterogeneity (outer bacteria — active, susceptible; inner bacteria — nutrient-deprived, slow metabolism → antibiotics targeting DNA replication, protein synthesis, cell wall synthesis are less effective on non-growing cells), persister cells (stochastically dormant subpopulation — survive antibiotic exposure → regrow when antibiotic removed → relapsing infections), horizontal gene transfer (close cell proximity → conjugation rates up to 1,000× higher within biofilm → rapid spread of resistance genes). (3) Clinical significance: ~80% of chronic bacterial infections involve biofilms: catheter infections (UTI, central line), dental plaque (caries, periodontal disease), lung infections in cystic fibrosis (Pseudomonas aeruginosa), prosthetic joint/implant infections, chronic wounds, endocarditis (heart valve). Treatment: often requires physical removal (catheter removal/replacement) + high-dose combination antibiotic therapy. (4) Quorum sensing: bacteria in biofilms communicate via chemical signals (autoinducers) → coordinate gene expression as a community (quorum sensing — discovered by Bonnie Bassler et al.).": "生物纤维:生物胶片——血清社区生活:(1)结构:细菌附着于表面,生产EPS(色素聚合物)基质 3D结构,配有水渠(营养质的交付) 成熟的生物纤维 生物纤维组成:多沙焦、蛋白质、细胞外细胞DNA(eDNA——结构性的血压)。 (2)抗药性机制:物理屏障(EPS防止抗生素渗透——缓慢的传播、吸附、基质的降解),代谢性异种(外菌细菌——活跃、易感性;内细菌-营养脱脂结构结构,慢新陈代谢,以DNA复制、蛋白合成、细胞壁状合成对非生长细胞、耐久细胞细胞(在抗生素性休眠亚基亚基)接触高抗生素接触时,水平基因移植(血清复发性感染后,细胞内血清接近性肾脏的血清迁移率(接近性细胞血清),在生物纤维细胞内更高程度内进行脱血解的治疗; 血解细胞细胞细胞细胞细胞循环循环循环迁移:血液内快速的血变异变、血液变变异变、血液变、血液变、血液变异变、血液变、血液变、血液变、血液