  "Outliers and Resistant Measures": "外围和抵抗措施",
  "Horizontal gene transfer (HGT) and antibiotic resistance: (1) Three mechanisms (unique to prokaryotes — no eukaryotic equivalent of this scale): (a) Transformation: competent bacteria uptake naked DNA from environment (released by dead cells). Natural competence in some species (S. pneumoniae, H. influenzae, B. subtilis). Griffith's experiment (1928) demonstrated transformation. (b) Conjugation: requires cell-to-cell contact. F plasmid encodes sex pilus → bridges donor (F⁺) to recipient (F⁻) → plasmid copy transferred → recipient becomes F⁺. Can transfer chromosomal genes (Hfr = high frequency recombination, when F integrates into chromosome). R plasmids (resistance) spread via conjugation — major clinical concern. (c) Transduction: bacteriophage packages host DNA fragments during lysis → injects into new host. Generalized (random host DNA) or specialized (specific genes near phage integration site). (2) MRSA: mecA gene on SCCmec (Staphylococcal Cassette Chromosome mec — a mobile genetic element). PBP2a: altered penicillin-binding protein with low β-lactam affinity → transpeptidase activity continues despite β-lactam presence → cell wall synthesis not inhibited. Treatment: vancomycin (Gram-positive → no outer membrane barrier), daptomycin, linezolid. VRSA (vancomycin-resistant) now emerging. (3) Global crisis: WHO lists antibiotic resistance as 'one of the biggest threats to global health' — ~700,000 deaths/year from resistant infections (projected ~10 million by 2050). HGT enables resistance to spread between species — unlike eukaryotic vertical (parent-to-offspring) inheritance.": "水平基因转移(HGT)和抗生素抗药性:(1) 三种机制(对prokaryotes而言是独一无二的):(1) 三种机制(对prokaryotes (F+) 性抗体-桥梁捐献者(F+) 向接受者(F-) 转基因(F+) ; 转基因: 有能力的细菌从环境中吸收赤裸的DNA(由死细胞释放); 某些物种的自然能力(S.肺炎、H.流感、B. supptilis) 。 Griffith的实验(1928年) 展示了一种转化性变化。 (b) 调试: 细菌包存放在解析期间的DNA碎片; 液化过程中的DNA捐献者(F+) 向接受者(F-) 转基因复制的(F+) ; 转基因复制的复制件(F+) 转基因基因组基因组基因组基因转移(Hfr=高频再基因组,当F融入染色体) 。",
  "What advantage does compartmentalization (membrane-bound organelles) provide to eukaryotic cells that prokaryotic cells lack?": "分层化(membrane-bounding organelles)对蛋白质细胞缺乏的表层细胞有什么好处?",
  "Compartmentalization advantage: (1) Specialized environments: lysosomes (pH 4.5 for hydrolysis), ER lumen (oxidizing for disulfide bonds), mitochondrial matrix (enzymes for citric acid cycle), peroxisomes (catalase for H₂O₂ detoxification). (2) Simultaneous incompatible reactions: protein synthesis (cytoplasm) AND protein degradation (lysosomes) can occur in the same cell without interference. (3) Increased surface area: cristae in mitochondria, thylakoids in chloroplasts — membranes increase area for membrane-bound reactions (ETC, photosystems). (4) Larger cell volume: prokaryotes are limited by surface area:volume ratio (all metabolic reactions occur at/near the plasma membrane). Eukaryotes overcome this with internal membranes that increase total reactive surface area. (5) Regulatory control: nuclear envelope separates transcription from translation — allows mRNA processing (splicing, capping, polyadenylation) before export — additional layer of gene regulation absent in prokaryotes. (6) Evolutionary consequence: eukaryotic compartmentalization (especially mitochondrial endosymbiosis) enabled the ~1,000-fold increase in genome size and cellular complexity that distinguishes eukaryotes from prokaryotes.": "遗传化优势:(1) 特殊环境: 淋病(pH4.5用于水解)、 ER 润滑剂(脱硫结合氧化物氧化)、 线粒体基质(柠檬酸循环的酶)、 过氧化体(H2O2脱毒的酸酶) 。 (2) 同步不相容反应: 蛋白合成(细胞质素)和蛋白降解(体质)可以在同一细胞中发生,不受干扰。 (3) 表面面积增加: 微粒状体、 叶绿石中的甲状腺—— 含膜反应(ETC, 光子系统) 的膜增加区域。 (4) 大细胞体体体体量: 体积比(在血浆membrane附近发生所有代谢反应) 。 Eukaryots通过内部膜来克服这一点,增加总反应表面积。 (5) 监管控制: 核信封分解与翻译—— 允许在基因变形变异基因变异基因变异变异变异变异性(摄像、 树质变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性) : 在基因变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变异性变的基因变变变异性(变异性变异性变的基因变性变性变形变形(制 )",
  "How do prokaryotic flagella fundamentally differ from eukaryotic flagella in structure and mechanism of movement?": "在流动结构和机制方面,质子旗子与eukaryaty旗子在结构上和在移动机制上有什么根本的不同?",
  "Flagella comparison — convergent evolution: (1) Prokaryotic flagellum: Structure: hollow tube of flagellin protein subunits (~20 nm diameter). Components: filament (flagellin), hook (flexible coupling), basal body (motor embedded in membrane/wall — stator and rotor rings). Mechanism: rotary motor powered by proton motive force (H⁺ flow through MotA/MotB stator). Speed: 100-1,000+ rpm. Direction: counterclockwise rotation → flagella bundle → 'run' (forward movement). Clockwise → flagella splay apart → 'tumble' (random reorientation). Chemotaxis: bacteria sense chemical gradients → adjust run/tumble frequency. (2) Eukaryotic flagellum/cilium: Structure: 9+2 axoneme — 9 outer doublet microtubules + 2 central singlets. Made of α/β-tubulin. ~250 nm diameter. Enclosed in plasma membrane extension. Mechanism: dynein motor proteins (molecular motors) cross-bridge between adjacent doublets → sliding → produces bending wave. Powered by ATP hydrolysis. Cilia: short, numerous, coordinated wavelike beating (e.g., respiratory epithelium). Flagella: long, few, undulating motion (e.g., sperm). (3) NOT homologous — completely different molecular composition, energy source, and mechanism. Same function (motility) arrived at independently = convergent evolution.": "红旗比较—— 凝固进化:(1) 质子体: 结构: 旗子蛋白分元件( ~ 20 nm 直径) 的空空空管。 部件: 丝状( 旗状) 、 钩形( 软体) 、 柱形体( 嵌入膜/ 壁—— 温度和旋转环) 。 机制: 由质子动力力( H+ 流动到 MotA/ MotB 结构) 驱动的旋转机动车。 速度: 100-1 000+ 。 方向: 直径( 向前移动) 的旗状( 旗状) 旗状( 旗状) 捆绑 的“ 跑 ” ( 向前移动 方向 ) 。 旗形( 旗状 旗状 ) 形形形体结构: 9+2 axoneme - 9 外双向微缩缩缩 + 2 中央单体 。 方向: 直径 直径 、 直径 直径 直径 直径 直径 、 直径 直径 内 内 等离 内 、 内 等离 型 型 型 型 型 、 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 、 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 、 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型 型",
  "Which definition BEST describes a flagellum?": "\" 最佳 \" 指的是什么定义?",
  "Flagellum — motility appendage with two distinct forms: (1) Prokaryotic flagellum: protein: flagellin. Structure: filament + hook + basal body (motor: rotor and stator rings embedded in membrane/wall). Energy: proton motive force (H⁺ gradient, or Na⁺ in marine bacteria). Mechanism: rotary motor — counterclockwise = 'run' (flagella bundle, forward swimming); clockwise = 'tumble' (flagella splay, random reorientation). Speed: up to 100+ body lengths/second. Chemotaxis: biased random walk toward attractants/away from repellents (mediated by MCPs → CheA/CheY signaling → flagellar motor switch). (2) Eukaryotic flagellum/cilium: protein: tubulin (α/β-tubulin heterodimers). Structure: 9+2 axoneme (9 outer doublets + 2 central singlets), nexin links, radial spokes, dynein arms. Covered by plasma membrane. Energy: ATP (dynein motor proteins). Mechanism: dynein walking causes doublet sliding → bending (restricted by nexin links). Cilia: short, numerous, coordinated beating (respiratory epithelium — mucociliary clearance). Flagella: long, few, undulating (sperm tail). (3) Key point: NOT homologous — completely independent origins. Same function arrived at by convergent evolution. Prokaryotic flagellar motor has been called 'the most efficient molecular machine known' — converts ~100% of input energy to output rotation.": "红旗——有两种不同的形式: (1) 红旗: 蛋白质; 白旗; 结构: 结构: 丝状 + 钩 + 钩 + basal 身体 (运动器: 嵌入膜膜/墙中的螺旋和螺纹环); 能量: 质子动力( H+ 梯度, 或海洋细菌中的纳+ + + ) 。 机制: 旋转马达- 逆时针 = 运行( 旗杆捆绑, 前方游泳); 顺时针 =“ 滚动 ” (旗杆 滚动, 随机调整方向调整方向)。 速度: 最多100+体身长/秒。 Chemotaxis: 有偏向吸引者/离开的任意行走动键( MCPs : CheA/ CheA/ CheY 信号发动机开关的标志 ) (2) 浮标/  蛋白质: 蛋白质(α (α ) 调、 电流质 电流动 动力 机 机 机 机 机 机 机 机 机 机 机 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部: 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机 机尾部 机尾部 机 机 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机 机 机尾部 机能 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机尾部 机 机 机尾部 机型 机尾部 。 。 机尾部 。 。 。 。 。 由 由 由 。 由 由 由 C. C. C. C. C. C",
  "A hospital microbiology lab receives a blood culture from a patient with high fever and suspected sepsis. The Gram stain shows Gram-negative rods. The physician immediately changes the antibiotic regimen from vancomycin to a broad-spectrum Gram-negative agent. Why does the Gram stain result change the treatment strategy, and what specific threats does a Gram-negative infection pose?": "医院微生物实验室从高发病和疑似败血症患者那里获得血液培养。Gram污点显示Gram阴性棒。医生立即将抗生素疗法从vancomycin 转变为 宽频谱Gram阴性制剂。 为什么Gram污点会改变治疗策略,而Gram阴性感染会构成什么具体威胁?",
  "Gram stain in clinical decision-making: (1) Why vancomycin fails against Gram-negatives: vancomycin (MW ~1,449 Da) works by binding D-Ala-D-Ala at the end of peptidoglycan precursor peptides → blocks cross-linking → cell wall synthesis fails → lysis. For Gram-positives: thick peptidoglycan exposed → vancomycin accesses target easily. For Gram-negatives: outer membrane acts as permeability barrier → vancomycin too large to penetrate porins (typically allow molecules <600-700 Da) → cannot reach peptidoglycan target. (2) Appropriate Gram-negative antibiotics: aminoglycosides (gentamicin — enter through porins + self-promoted uptake), fluoroquinolones (ciprofloxacin — penetrate porins), β-lactams with outer membrane penetration (aztreonam — monobactam), carbapenems (meropenem — small enough + resistant to most β-lactamases). (3) LPS/endotoxin threat: Lipid A component of LPS → triggers TLR4 on macrophages → massive cytokine release (TNF-α, IL-1β, IL-6) → systemic inflammatory response (SIRS) → sepsis → septic shock (vasodilation, hypotension, organ failure) → mortality 30-50%. Even dead Gram-negative bacteria release LPS → antibiotic-mediated bacterial killing can initially worsen sepsis (Jarisch-Herxheimer reaction). (4) Time is critical in sepsis: every hour of delayed appropriate antibiotics increases mortality by ~7.6%. The Gram stain provides actionable information within 15-30 minutes — vs. culture (48-72 hrs).": "在临床决策中,血压变色器在临床决策中失灵:(1) 为何Vancomycin对Gram-Negaticals:在Peptidogicac 前体peptides 块块交叉连接的细胞墙合成失败解析。对于血压阳剂:厚的peptidoglycan暴露于Vancomycin 进入目标。对于Gram-Negagy:外膜的血压作为渗透性屏障(MW~1,449 Da),由D-Ala-D-Ala在Peptidogoceptides Pepticides Pepticides Pepticides (血压+自我促进摄入)、氟丙酮(crofroxisionacin-渗透性pormains) , xem-emia-embrane 反渗透性反应(Azrealam-toimal-Ital-Imadeal-Ideal-Iam-Imadeal-Istal-Istal-L-Imadeal-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-lisal-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-l-",
  "Robert Koch (Nobel Prize 1905) established his famous postulates to prove that a specific microorganism causes a specific disease. He used these criteria to identify Mycobacterium tuberculosis as the causative agent of tuberculosis and Bacillus anthracis for anthrax. What are Koch's postulates, and what are their modern limitations?": "罗伯特·科奇(Nobel奖(1905年))建立了他著名的假设,以证明特定微生物导致特定疾病。 他用这些标准来确定Mycobactirium 结核病是结核病和炭疽杆菌炭疽病的诱因。 科奇的假设是什么,现代限制是什么?",
  "Koch's postulates — foundation of medical microbiology: (1) Robert Koch (1843-1910): German physician. Identified causative agents of: anthrax (Bacillus anthracis, 1876), tuberculosis (Mycobacterium tuberculosis, 1882), cholera (Vibrio cholerae, 1883). Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine, 1905. (2) Postulates (formalized 1884): (a) Association: pathogen present in all disease cases, absent from healthy hosts. (b) Isolation: pathogen isolated from diseased host, grown in pure culture. (c) Causation: pure culture causes disease in new susceptible host. (d) Re-isolation: same pathogen re-isolated from experimentally infected host. (3) Limitations: unculturable pathogens (Mycobacterium leprae — causes leprosy — never grown in pure culture; Treponema pallidum — syphilis), asymptomatic carriers (Salmonella typhi — 'Typhoid Mary' — healthy carrier), ethical constraints (cannot inoculate humans with deadly pathogens), polymicrobial diseases (multiple organisms required), viral diseases (Koch worked before virology matured), host factors (genetic susceptibility, immune status). (4) Modern adaptations: molecular Koch's postulates (Stanley Falkow, 1988): (a) virulence gene present in pathogenic strains, absent from avirulent; (b) gene inactivation → loss of virulence; (c) restoration of gene → restores virulence. Used with: transposon mutagenesis, gene knockouts, complementation studies. (5) Legacy: Koch's work established germ theory on solid experimental ground and created the template for identifying causative agents of infectious diseases.": "科赫的假设——医学微生物学的基础:(1) 罗伯特·科奇(1843-1910):德国医生;查明炭疽(炭疽杆菌,1876)、肺结核(肺结核,1882年)、霍乱(霍乱,1883年);1905年诺贝尔生理学或医学奖;(2) 配方(正规化为1884年): (a) 协会:所有疾病病例中的病原体存在,没有健康宿主; (b) 脱氧:疾病宿主的病原体分离,在纯文化中成长;(c) 致癌:纯文化导致新易感染宿主的疾病;(d) 致癌:病原生重新与实验受感染宿主隔离。 (3) 限制:不易培养的病原体(肿瘤 Leprade-导致麻风病在纯文化中从未生长); Treponemalema taltual dium-Meminedrial。 (Treality) 止痛病原原体的病原体变变变原体,(血变变原体前的血变原体) 血变原体病原体病原体病原体病变变原体病变原病原体的病原病变 (癌症) (癌症) 病变变原体病变原病变原病变原病变原病变原病变原病变原病变原病变原体的病原病原病原病原病原